properties.areaDesc: North Snowy Range Foothills; South Laramie Range Foothills; South Laramie Range; Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 16 at 3:35AM MST until January 18 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 40 to 50 mph with gusts up to 75 mph.

* WHERE...Interstate 80 between Rawlins and Cheyenne, and
Interstate 25 between Chugwater and Wheatland.

* WHEN...5 AM MST Friday until 8 AM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous for
light and high profile vehicles, including camping and tractor
trailers. There will be a high risk for blow overs, especially
on north to south oriented roads.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING
